name: Donte ROLLINS, Petitioner v. COURT OF COMMON PLEAS OF PHILADELPHIA COUNTY, Respondent
name_abbreviation: Rollins v. Court of Common Pleas of Philadelphia County

parties: Donte ROLLINS, Petitioner v. COURT OF COMMON PLEAS OF PHILADELPHIA COUNTY, Respondent.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 1st day of September, 2016, the Application for Leave to File Original Process is GRANTED.
The Petition for Writs of Mandamus and Prohibition is DENIED, WITHOUT PREJUDICE to Petitioner to pursue similar relief in this Court following the impending hearings before the common pleas court.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.

145 A.3d 720
Donte ROLLINS, Petitioner v. COURT OF COMMON PLEAS OF PHILADELPHIA COUNTY, Respondent.
No. 108 EM 2016.
